I ordered 3 tacos today, 1 shrimp and 2 chicken, and I was very dissatisfied. The cashier is rude and dishonest- he copped an attitude when I questioned him about upcharges at the end of the transaction. I like to support local businesses, but local businesses must have good customer service in order to maintain patronage. Their food isn't even good enough to warrant the attitude. The chicken tacos were gross, no seasoning at all. I think they just grilled the chicken with olive oil. No salt, black paper, garlic, NOTHING. The additions (tomato and lettuce) taste and looked old. The pieces of shrimp were overcooked but at least that had some flavor. There aren't many quality Mexican spots in the West Bronx but I'm willing to travel to Queens or Manhattan if this is what they have to offer. By the way I'm a life long Bronxite, so this is hurts my heart. Lol. Save your money and go somewhere else folks
